attributes.name: Vecht valley route: follow the Vecht to Germany
attributes.description: This LF route of 245 kilometers from Zwolle follows the Vecht to Darfeld in Germany, in seven stages. The first route starts in the Hanseatic city of Zwolle. From here you cycle to the estate village of Vilsteren, through old forests with beautiful villas and castles. At Ommen and Hardenberg, large contiguous forest areas alternate with beautiful farming communities, such as Junne, Beerze, Diffelen and Rheeze. Make a stop in Hardenberg at the cozy Boomstamrestaurant Het Heemse! Then you cross the border, past historic towns such as Gramsbergen, to a beautiful landscape of old farms with fruit trees. On the fourth stretch, you cross the Vecht many times. Via Bad Bentheim you cycle to the park landscape of Münsterland. Here the river can be found in bowls, bordered by old vegetation: this stream valley landscape is protected in many places.
attributes.shortDescription: Wil jij het Vechtdal ontdekken? Dan is deze LF-route van 245 kilometer van Zwolle naar het Duitse Darfeld iets voor jou. Al fietsend volg je de loop van de Vecht in zeven etappes. Verdeel deze etappes over verschillende dagen en maak kennis met de landschappen en gezellige plaatsjes op deze route. Het eerste traject start in de Hanzestad Zwolle. Vanuit hier fiets je naar Vilsteren door schitterende oude landgoedbossen. Vervolgens fiets je door de bossen verder naar Hardenberg. Daarna is het tijd om de Duitse grens over te steken. Op het derde traject kun je een pauze inlassen bij Granny's Barn Hadassa Hoeve in Ane voor een hapje en een drankje. Vervolgens fiets je verder naar Nordhorn en daarna naar Schüttorf en Metelen. Je eindigt uiteindelijk in Darfeld.

attributes.name: Lunchroom en bakkerij Van der Most – Dalfsen
attributes.description: Bakery Lunchroom Van der Most has been a household name in the nature-rich Vechtdal for many years. The company has lunch cafes in the towns of Ommen, Dalfsen, Raalte and Lemelerveld. You can enjoy a drink and pastry, freshly filled sandwiches and regional products such as Dalfser Moppen, Sallandse wine and the homemade Vechtdal pasta in every location. Curious about the secret behind the delicious chocolates and cakes? Then follow a workshop at the bakery. Go out in the Vechtdal, taste the peace and park your bike at Van der Most to satisfy your appetite.

attributes.name: B&B De Rheezer Kamer Thee- en Koffiehuis
attributes.description: B&B De Rheezer Kamer Thee- en Koffiehuis is located in one of the most beautiful places in the Overijssel Vechtdal. As a cycling and nature lover you will be surprised from one surprise to another because of the picturesque landscapes that this area is rich in. Just like the Vechtdal, De Rheezer Kamer is the ideal place to relax. On the terrace you can enjoy the view over the historic village green with a real Italian Agust Coffee and delicious homemade cake. And in the former barn you will experience how peaceful you can stay in the countryside.

attributes.name: Granny's Barn Hadassa Hoeve
attributes.description: Granny\\\'s Barn Hadassa Hoeve is a cozy tea house in Ane. This break spot is located on the edge of the Pieterpad and in the middle of beautiful green areas that are ideal for a bike ride or a walk. Settle down at Granny\\\'s Barn to catch your breath during an active day and enjoy one of Grandma's many teas, a cup of coffee or homemade treats such as an apple dumpling or a delicious slice of cake. It's like stepping into your own grandmother's house. In addition to sweets, you will also find ice cream, sandwiches, soup and much more to satisfy your appetite. Replenish your energy supply well, so that you can hit the road again afterwards. When the weather is nice you can take a seat on the outside terrace to enjoy the sun. At the teahouse you will also find a shop with old-fashioned sweets and nice trinkets to give as gifts.
